social_posts.post_text:
You know what i love about the words on my shirt? Is the last sentence “it’s time to heal.” I encountered a woman who was doing everything in her power to bark up my tree and push me out of my grace but the difference between her and I, is that my healing isn’t in my words but actions. I stood there  while she tried to use my past against me as if I’m not the reason that allowed for everyone to know about my past?! I don’t hide from who i was when i was a boy but i speak on it now and allow my story to encourage both men and woman. With that being said if you want to change you will, you can and most importantly, you must! But it has to be on your own doing not someone’s else’s. 
Last thing I’m proud of who i am and the work I’ve put into myself.🤍
This kid will make a lot of people lives better whenever he enters their life. @cwoods1212 #upsyndrome 💛💙

God is good, my spirit is great, my mental health has progressively moved forward. My physical health is getting back to a healthier lifestyle. Every day is a step maybe not a big one but nonetheless it’s a step in the right direction
Mi madre! @gc_maryj love you and not just on one day but everyday. Thank you for being there for me at my highest and lowest.🤍
